HEADWORD: Rupee
<hw>Ru*pee"</hw> <pr>(r⟦usdot⟧*p⟦emac⟧")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Hind.
<ets>r⟦umac⟧piyah</ets>, fr. Skr. <ets>r⟦umac⟧pya</ets> silver, coined
silver or gold, handsome.]</ety> <def>A silver coin, and money of
account, in the East Indies.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The valuation of the rupee of sixteen annas, the
standard coin of India, by the United States Treasury department, varies
from time to time with the price of silver. In 1889 it was rated at
about thirty-two cents.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rupellary</ent>⟦br⟧
